Buoyed by its 1-0 away victory against Ojodu Champions FC in Week 2 of the ongoing Lagos State Football Association 2021/2022 Nationwide League (Division One) season, FirstBank FC is expected to carry on the victory runs when they confront Collins Edwin FC in Week 3 encounter. Billed for the Nitel Football pitch in the Cappa area of Oshodi, the 90-minute encounter is expected to bring out the best from the Elephants Boys.   Fanfare as winners emerge in FirstBank International Horse…     Chelsea Supporters’ Trust not backing Ricketts family’s bid…     AFFAN unveils first netball court in Nigeria   Star player, Saheed Egbeolowo who has two goals to his credit is expected to lead the attack for the Bankers in the Monday morning clash. A home win against Yobo FC in the season’s opener and the away victory recorded against Ojodu Champions last weekend are all the Elephant Boys needed to maintain their position on the league table. Though it’s too early to guess where the league’s trophy would be heading at the end of the season, analysts are of the opinion that, if FirstBank FC keep the momentum, they might be competing in the upper cadre next season.